    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#GC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name>Ἄλκιμος</name></persName> ἔγλυψε
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text derived from photograph</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#GC">
                <p>Alkimos engraved.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Vermeule and Comstock suggest that the relief style implies that Alkimos was perhaps a coin die engraver; they also note that the eight-point star first appears in Sicily on Syracusan coinage from c.400 BCE. For the museum's record (Sculpture in Stone (MFA), no. 089; Sculpture in Stone and Bronze (MFA), p. 109) see <ref target="https://collections.mfa.org/objects/151092">https://collections.mfa.org/objects/151092</ref></p>
            </div>
